overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetics
  of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. The
  agent conducted a detailed review of the existing styling, identifying areas
  such as the color palette, layout, typography, and form elements that needed
  refinement. The approach involved implementing a new, calming sleep-themed
  color palette using OKLCH, introducing subtle background elements, and
  redesigning key UI components like progress bars, cards, checkboxes, radio
  buttons, and sliders for a more polished look. All questionnaire sections were
  updated to ensure consistent styling, replacing generic gray boxes with themed
  card-like groupings. The report section also received a visual refresh with
  consistent gradient headers and theme-aligned text colors. Additionally, a
  console error related to  values being passed to input fields was
  identified and resolved by modifying the  component to handle
  gracefully. The outcome is a visually cohesive, professional, and calming
  application that aligns with the sleep health theme.
